{
  "info": {
    "name": "Hermes API",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the Hermes job portal backend.\n\n**Base URL:** `http://localhost:5001/api/v1`\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Set the `base_url` variable to your backend address\n2. Run `POST /auth/login` — `access_token` and `refresh_token` are set automatically\n3. All protected routes use `Bearer {{access_token}}`\n\n**Response envelope:**\n- Success: `{\"success\": true, \"data\": {...}}`\n- Error: `{\"success\": false, \"error\": {\"code\", \"message\", \"details\", \"timestamp\", \"request_id\"}}`\n\n**Token rotation:** If the server returns an `X-New-Access-Token` header, replace `access_token` with its value.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:5001/api/v1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "access_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "refresh_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "reset_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Password reset token received from forgot-password email"
    },
    {
      "key": "verify_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Email verification token received in registration email"
    },
    {
      "key": "job_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "notification_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "user_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Check if the backend API is running. No authentication required."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Handle proactive token rotation",
                  "const newToken = pm.response.headers.get('X-New-Access-Token');",
                  "if (newToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', newToken);",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.data.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.data.refresh_token);",
                  "  pm.test('Returns user object without password_hash', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.user).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.user).to.have.property('email');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.user).to.not.have.property('password_hash');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Request-ID", "value": "req_register_001", "description": "Optional — used for tracing in error responses" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePass123!\",\n  \"full_name\": \"John Doe\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Register a new user account.\n\n**Rate limit:** 5 requests/minute per IP.\n\n**Returns:** `{success, data: {user, access_token, refresh_token}}`\n\n**Errors:**\n- `400 VALIDATION_ERROR` — missing/invalid fields or unknown fields in body\n- `400 VALIDATION_EMAIL_EXISTS` — email already registered"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Handle proactive token rotation",
                  "const newToken = pm.response.headers.get('X-New-Access-Token');",
                  "if (newToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', newToken);",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.data.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.data.refresh_token);",
                  "  pm.test('Response has token pair', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('access_token');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('refresh_token');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Request-ID", "value": "req_login_001" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePass123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Login with email and password. Automatically sets `access_token` and `refresh_token` collection variables.\n\n**Rate limit:** 5 requests/minute per IP.\n\n**Returns:** `{success, data: {access_token, refresh_token}}`\n\n**Errors:**\n- `401 AUTH_INVALID_CREDENTIALS` — wrong email or password\n- `401 AUTH_ACCOUNT_SUSPENDED` — account suspended by admin"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.data.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.data.refresh_token);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{refresh_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/refresh",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "refresh"]
            },
            "description": "Exchange the refresh token for a new access + refresh token pair. The old refresh token JTI is blocklisted after rotation.\n\n**Auth:** Requires the **refresh** token in Authorization header (not the access token).\n\n**Returns:** `{success, data: {access_token, refresh_token}}`\n\n**Errors:**\n- `401 AUTH_UNAUTHORIZED` — token is an access token, not a refresh token\n- `401 AUTH_TOKEN_REVOKED` — refresh token was already used or logged out"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', '');",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', '');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/logout",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "logout"]
            },
            "description": "Invalidate the current access token by adding its JTI to the Redis blocklist. Clears both token variables on success.\n\n**Auth:** JWT required.\n\n**Errors:**\n- `401 AUTH_UNAUTHORIZED` — no token provided\n- `401 AUTH_TOKEN_REVOKED` — token already blocklisted"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Forgot Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/forgot-password",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "forgot-password"]
            },
            "description": "Request a password reset email. Always returns 200 regardless of whether the email is registered — this prevents account enumeration.\n\n**Returns:** `{success, data: {message}}`\n\n**Token TTL:** 1 hour (stored in Redis).\n\n**Errors:**\n- `400 VALIDATION_ERROR` — invalid email format"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Reset Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"{{reset_token}}\",\n  \"new_password\": \"NewSecurePass456!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/reset-password",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "reset-password"]
            },
            "description": "Submit a new password using the reset token received by email. The token is single-use and deleted from Redis after a successful reset.\n\n**Returns:** `{success, data: {message}}`\n\n**Errors:**\n- `400 VALIDATION_ERROR` — password < 8 chars or missing token\n- `400 AUTH_INVALID_TOKEN` — token is invalid or has expired"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify Email",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/verify-email/{{verify_token}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "verify-email", "{{verify_token}}"]
            },
            "description": "Verify the user's email address using the token sent after registration. The token is single-use (deleted from Redis on success) with a 24-hour TTL.\n\n**Returns:** `{success, data: {message}}`\n\n**Errors:**\n- `400 AUTH_INVALID_TOKEN` — token is invalid or has expired"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
